Description: A very nice 1996 MIM Fender Duo-Sonic short scale guitar. Looks great and fun to play! Body Dated Feb 20 1996 and Neck Mar 27 1996. The neck has a beautiful aged look and is in great condition - frets have been leveled and polished and look very good. Body has the expected scratches & minor dings for a guitar of this vintage. The only large scar is a gouge in the guitar body edge just below the cable jack. See pictures. It wasn't filled and smoothed but the paint match is very good. Also, there is a chip in the finish alongside the bottom strap connector. Other than that the guitar looks great. A very nice shiny red. A few minor dings in the lower back of the neck - not at all serious. Please zoom into the pictures. The pickguard has been upgraded to a 3-ply and the pickup selector to a high quality CTS switch. Electronics all work fine. Payment is due promptly at end of auction. If you cannot comply, please do not bid. Item is guaranteed as described – otherwise non-returnable. I generally ship by the end of the next business day. Please look at pictures closely – I do my best to photograph and what you see is what you get! Sale is for the guitar only - no additional accessories. And do contact me if you have any questions or wood like any additional detail. Thank you!
Title: Fender Duo-Sonic Electric Guitar -1996 - Torino Red - Made in Mexico. Nice!
